<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">Allows a user to log in for OAuth authorization purposes by authenticating with an identity provider that has its own login screen, providing SSO is enabled for the OAuth Provider and the identity provider it's using. Examples: Facebook, Google. Sets the <a href="../aaref/Ref_CookiesOnThePlatform.htm">OAuthToken_{OAuthProviderName}</a> cookie and redirects the user. Also for LDAP users. Uses HTTP POST.